hashCode() - Method in interface PersonInterface
compute the hash code of Person key is phone number, phone number is a string in the form:
(XXX)XXX-XXXX hashcode = (p1 * (areaCode + p2 * exchangeCode) + extensionCode) p1 is the prime 23 and p2 is the prime 31 In the phone number (555)123-4567 areaCode = 555 exchangeCode = 123 extensionCode = 4567
hashKey(String) - Static method in class Person

HashTable<T extends PersonInterface> - Class in <Unnamed>
This class provides a hash table used to store Person objects in an address book utility The hash table is implemented as an array of LinkedLists that contain PersonInterface objects Uses buckets to store objects with the same hash code
